theorem interior_diff_eq_of_closed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hB : IsClosed B) :
    interior (A \ B) = interior A \ B := by
  -- We establish mutual inclusion of the two sets.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- First, show `interior (A \ B) ⊆ interior A \ B`.
    intro x hx
    have h₁ :=
      (interior_diff_subset (X := X) (A := A) (B := B)) hx
    -- Since `B` is closed, `closure B = B`.
    simpa [hB.closure_eq] using h₁
  · -- Conversely, show `interior A \ B ⊆ interior (A \ B)`.
    rintro x ⟨hxIntA, hxNotB⟩
    -- Choose an open neighborhood `U` of `x` contained in `A`.
    rcases (Set.mem_interior).1 hxIntA with ⟨U, hU_open, hU_subA, hxU⟩
    -- Consider the open set `U \ B`.
    have hU'open : IsOpen (U \ B) := by
      -- `Bᶜ` is open because `B` is closed.
      have hOpenCompl : IsOpen (Bᶜ) := hB.compl
      -- `U \ B = U ∩ Bᶜ`.
      simpa [Set.diff_eq] using hU_open.inter hOpenCompl
    -- `x` belongs to `U \ B`.
    have hxU' : x ∈ U \ B := by
      exact ⟨hxU, hxNotB⟩
    -- `U \ B` is contained in `A \ B`.
    have hU'subset : U \ B ⊆ A \ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact ⟨hU_subA hy.1, hy.2⟩
    -- Hence `x ∈ interior (A \ B)`.
    exact
      (Set.mem_interior).2 ⟨U \ B, hU'open, hU'subset, hxU'⟩

import Mathlib

open Set

variable {α : Type*} [TopologicalSpace α]

theorem interior_inter_closure_self (s : Set α) :
    interior s ∩ closure s = interior s := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    exact hx.1
  · intro hx
    exact And.intro hx (subset_closure hx)

theorem isOpen_diff_closed_imp_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) (hB : IsClosed B) :
    Topology.P1 (A \ B) := by
  -- `A \ B` can be written as the intersection of the open set `A`
  -- and the open complement of the closed set `B`.
  have hOpenDiff : IsOpen (A \ B) := by
    -- The complement of a closed set is open.
    have hOpenCompl : IsOpen (Bᶜ) := by
      simpa using (isOpen_compl_iff).2 hB
    -- The intersection of two open sets is open.
    simpa [Set.diff_eq] using hA.inter hOpenCompl
  -- Any open set satisfies `P1`.
  simpa using
    Topology.isOpen_imp_P1 (X := X) (A := A \ B) hOpenDiff
